If you’re a mostly healthy person who contracts the coronavirus, will letting your fever run high help get rid of it?
… Only high temperatures kill a virus, so let your fever run high.
There have been some claims that using ibuprofen to treat coronavirus symptoms is risky.
And it isn’t yet known whether a fever might help the body fight the novel coronavirus, as it does other viruses.
The advice on letting a fever run high to fight the coronavirus, even with generally healthy people and mild to moderate respiratory symptoms, is too broad.